                            <comment id="36287" author="nmervaillie" created="Thu, 29 May 2008 20:36:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran into this issue as well and had it work with this patch.&lt;br/&gt;
Please note that classIdentityQuery &amp;amp; sidIdentityQuery have to be overridden with postgres specific queries in your bean definition.&lt;br/&gt;
I ran the tests and everything seems fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nicolas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="36501" author="balex" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2008 13:57:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a known issue with Postgres. Some references for those interested in learning more about this Postgres requirement:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://sql-info.de/en/postgresql/postgres-gotchas.html#1_1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://sql-info.de/en/postgresql/postgres-gotchas.html#1_1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/sql-select.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/sql-select.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have applied the patch, as it tested fine with Hypersonic. Postgres users should note they will still need to call the mutator methods (setters) to use the different sequence number allocation stored procedure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SVN revision number 3131.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
